13/09/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The body of a police officer killed by torrential rains and floods on the island of Evia was recovered on Saturday (September 12th). 
The man, around 40 years old, was found in his car which was swept away by the rising waters of a river near the town of Kimi. 
Traffic on the island has been seriously affected by the rains, which have flooded many roads and houses. 
(AFP, AP - 12/09/09)
